      "side": 1,
      "message": "Oh, yeah, I think we\u0027re okay here for now.\n\nI was thinking that dstCS could be the same but fColor could be different, but obviously we also make the SkShader* part of the key, so fColor will always match.  I may end up pushing up against this again later as I try to reuse programs between, say, two SkColorShaders, but for now we\u0027re good.\n\nThough I guess to actually be safe here the cache should hold a ref on the pointery parts of the key while they\u0027re in the cache, or we could accidentally think a living shader is the same as a dead one.",
